newsitem.title: USA: Six firms win $100 mln Westchester Cty, N.Y., TANs. [corrected 20:34 gmt]
newsitem.headline: Six firms win $100 mln Westchester Cty, N.Y., TANs. [corrected 20:34 gmt]

text.p: Six firms won $100 million of Westchester County, N.Y., tax anticipation notes sold competitively on Thursday.

PaineWebber Inc won $50 million with a 3.49 percent coupon; JP Morgan Securities won $25 million with a 3.48 percent coupon; Roosevelt & Cross Inc won $10 million with a 3.48 percent coupon; Lehman Brothers won $5 million with a 3.47 percent coupon; First Union Capital Markets won $5 million with a 3.48 percent coupon; and BNY Capital Markets Inc (corrects from Bank of New York) won $5 million with a 3.50 percent coupon.
